#Text=Later , it was known as the location of the Spring Creek Raid , sometimes called the Battle of Ten Sleep , one of the last  Wild West " battles . ( You can find a historical marker commemorating this south of town on WY 434 . )

column1: #Text=Today , Ten Sleep is a common stop for tourists on their way to the Bighorn Mountains , Yellowstone National Park , or ( in the other direction ) Sturgis .
#Text=The surrounding lands also attract many hunters and fishers .
#Text=Unless you really know the local backroads well , you 'll come in on US 16 and you 'll leave that way too .
#Text=From the west , US 16 passes through Worland , the nearest " big city .
